"title": "7464: teachers of the law",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7464: teachers of the law",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Those professionally trained to develop, teach and apply the OT law. In the application of the law the oral teaching of these people often assumed greater authority than the written law. Thus, by the time of the NT, the teachers of the law were in conflict with Jesus Christ and the apostles, who taught with authority and condemned the outward religious acts that the teachers had fostered.</p>\n<h2>Teachers of the law mentioned by name</h2>\n<h3>Ezra</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:1-Ezra7:21\">EZR 7:1–7:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:1-Neh8:18\">NEH 8:1–8:18</a> <em>Teachers of the law arose after the exile from amongst the earlier scribes whose duties were more strictly secretarial.</em></p>\n<h3>Nicodemus</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:10\">JHN 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>Gamaliel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:34\">ACT 5:34</a> <em>Teachers of the law belonged mainly to the Pharisees but as a body were distinct from them.</em></p>\n<h2>Teachers of the law in conflict with Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Concerning righteousness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:20\">MAT 5:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Concerning Jesus Christ's authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:2-Matt9:8\">MAT 9:2–9:8</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:5-Mark2:12\">MRK 2:5–2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:20-Luke5:26\">LUK 5:20–5:26</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:22-Mark3:27\">MRK 3:22–3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:27-Mark11:33\">MRK 11:27–11:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:1-Luke20:8\">LUK 20:1–20:8</a></p>\n<h3>Concerning the seeking of signs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:38-Matt12:39\">MAT 12:38–12:39</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Concerning hypocrisy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:2-Matt23:33\">MAT 23:2–23:33</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:38-Mark12:40\">MRK 12:38–12:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:34-Luke13:35\">LUK 13:34–13:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:46\">LUK 20:46</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:1-Matt15:8\">MAT 15:1–15:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:1-Mark7:8\">MRK 7:1–7:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:13\">ISA 29:13</a></p>\n<h3>Concerning the children's praise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:15-Matt21:16\">MAT 21:15–21:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:2\">PSA 8:2</a></p>\n<h3>Concerning Jesus Christ's mixing with sinners</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:16-Mark2:17\">MRK 2:16–2:17</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:30-Luke5:32\">LUK 5:30–5:32</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:1-Luke15:7\">LUK 15:1–15:7</a></p>\n<h3>Concerning Jesus Christ's identity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:35-Mark12:37\">MRK 12:35–12:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a></p>\n<h3>Concerning the Sabbath</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:7-Luke6:11\">LUK 6:7–6:11</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The teachers of the law sought to get rid of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>By falsely accusing him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:10\">LUK 23:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:57-Matt26:60\">MAT 26:57–26:60</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:53-Mark14:56\">MRK 14:53–14:56</a> <em>The teachers of the law were entrusted with the administration of the law as judges in the Sanhedrin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:3-John8:6\">JHN 8:3–8:6</a></p>\n<h3>By looking for ways to arrest and kill him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:18\">MRK 11:18</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:47\">LUK 19:47</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:1\">MRK 14:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:2\">LUK 22:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:43\">MRK 14:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:19\">LUK 20:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:12\">MRK 12:12</a></p>\n<h3>By sending him to be tried before Pilate</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:1\">MRK 15:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:66-Luke23:1\">LUK 22:66–23:1</a></p>\n<h2>The teachers of the law, with others, mocked Christ crucified</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:41-Matt27:42\">MAT 27:41–27:42</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:31-Mark15:32\">MRK 15:31–15:32</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ foretold the opposition of the teachers of the law</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:18-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:18–20:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:33-Mark10:34\">MRK 10:33–10:34</a></p>\n<h2>Teachers of the law in conflict with the apostles</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:5-Acts4:7\">ACT 4:5–4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:12\">ACT 6:12</a></p>\n<h2>Teachers of the law in a non-confrontational setting</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:4\">MAT 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:19-Matt8:20\">MAT 8:19–8:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:52\">MAT 13:52</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:39\">LUK 20:39</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:7\">1TI 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:28-Matt7:29\">MAT 7:28–7:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:10\">MAT 17:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:11\">MRK 9:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:22\">MRK 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:9\">ACT 23:9</a></p>",
